Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.78,0:00:19.91,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't supposed to be \Nlike this, head in my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.37,0:00:26.25,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Struggling to escape from \Nthis saturated world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.84,0:00:32.01,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes like whispering sand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:35.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,These circumstances, unchanging
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.72,0:00:38.72,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,gazing out at a dreamless tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.64,0:00:45.81,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna say goodbye to the \Nconfusion of yesterday
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.19,0:00:51.23,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,I try reaching out, as if to resist
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.53,0:00:56.95,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,We cry millions of times \Nand then get born again
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.24,0:01:00.16,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go with these red eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.16,0:01:03.37,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,to that pictured future
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.37,0:01:08.96,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Come here right by me, \NI'm clapping my hands
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.13,0:01:11.05,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you? Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.05,0:01:15.42,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Strain my eyes in the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.42,0:01:21.06,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,Can't see anything, don't know \Nanything, but I'll still go
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.31,0:01:27.39,Song,Opening Song,0000,0000,0000,,To the place of shining \Nlight in which you wait
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.39,0:01:29.98,Episode Num,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.39,0:01:29.98,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku's Funeral
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.39,0:01:29.98,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by Ango Sakaguchi's\NMeijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Detective Stories)\N "Sneering Demon" and "Red Trap"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.78,0:01:35.94,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't like you...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.94,0:01:37.07,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,'Course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.53,0:01:40.78,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,As always, the second I \Nunravel the whole thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.16,0:01:41.70,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.16,0:01:41.70,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.78,0:01:42.24,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou goes to cover it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.24,0:01:45.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I have to get him in public, \Nthat is, on live TV,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.95,0:01:46.08,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Sasa Kazamori
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.95,0:01:46.08,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Artificial Intelligence (R.A.I.)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.12,0:01:47.16,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,where he can't talk his way out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.16,0:01:49.96,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Do you dislike Kaishou \NRinroku that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.58,0:01:52.71,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to reveal the truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.25,0:01:56.51,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Were you interested in the \Ntruth in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:02.64,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,According to Inga, you \Nbecame a detective for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.64,0:02:03.47,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.14,0:02:06.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,I became a detective to \Nlearn people's truths.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.39,0:02:10.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Because that's the only thing I can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.02,0:02:13.61,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,"People's truths." \NThose are souls, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.61,0:02:17.40,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,You promised Inga that you'd \Nkeep giving him souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.40,0:02:19.74,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that why you became a detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.49,0:02:24.58,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Inga isn't here now, so is it necessary \Nto seek out the truth any longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:27.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou is using Bettenou.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.45,0:02:28.87,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Can I let him do whatever he pleases?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.33,0:02:30.58,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Well, about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.29,0:02:33.54,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.30,0:02:45.14,Caption Top,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Kantou TV
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.73,0:02:51.48,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,This is just one example of simulated \Nfootage that's all over the net.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:51.65,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Kuramitsu Mine
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:51.65,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,New Diet Member
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.81,0:02:54.65,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Does it have something to do with \Nwhatever destroyed the TV station that day?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.65,0:02:58.61,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Many of these videos advance the \Nhypothesis that a microwave weapon was used...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:01.74,Main Dialog,Chairman,0000,0000,0000,,I call the witness, Mr. Kaishou Rinroku.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.78,0:03:05.53,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place, microwaves \Nand electromagnetic waves
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.53,0:03:07.12,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,can't be seen by the naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.54,0:03:14.50,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,The power density of microwave \Ntransmissions is at best
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:17.84,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,23 milliwatts per square centimeter,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.84,0:03:21.01,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,which is less than a hundredth the \Npower of a microwave oven in the home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:23.59,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:26.76,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,According to the company's documents \Nthat were leaked by Full Circle...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:28.93,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,These are genuine, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:32.94,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,In here, the experimental value \Nis several hundred megawatts.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:35.31,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,You can't even compare \Novens to that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.44,0:03:38.61,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,That refers to the total \Nlifetime capacity,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.61,0:03:41.24,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,and comparing it to the transmission \Nrate makes no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:43.57,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand the nuts and bolts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.57,0:03:45.70,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,but foreign nations \Nhave also pointed out
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.70,0:03:48.29,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,that this technology could be \Napplied to weaponry, haven't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.29,0:03:51.66,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Since when was JJ Systems \Na weapons manufacturer?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:04:00.17,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Kaishou Rinroku
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.54,0:04:00.17,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Chairman of JJ Systems
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.17,0:03:56.50,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,In 2001...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:04:00.21,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone watched the scene of passenger \Njets flying into buildings,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.21,0:04:01.55,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,and yet soon after came \Nconspiracy theories
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.55,0:04:02.93,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,of the buildings being \Nblown up on purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:05.80,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Some even believed preposterous \Nideas involving hydrogen bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.43,0:04:11.06,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,In 2011 these influences still remain,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.06,0:04:14.27,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,with some people convinced \Nthat natural disasters
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.27,0:04:16.56,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,are due to an "earthquake \Nweapon", of all things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.36,0:04:19.69,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Why is the detective...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.44,0:04:19.69,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Kaishou Rie
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.44,0:04:19.69,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Daughter of Kaishou Rinroku, Lives at Home
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.23,0:04:23.82,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,People tend to think that \Nthe truth is hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.49,0:04:28.83,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,And there are people who believe that \Nonly they have arrived at the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.54,0:04:31.91,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,But there are an innumerable \Nnumber of truths.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.37,0:04:35.12,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Being satisfied with just one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.12,0:04:37.92,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,is no more than ceasing to think \Nabout it beyond that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.50,0:04:40.00,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.42,0:04:43.97,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Is he trying to twist the \Ntruth with Bettenou's power?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.34,0:04:45.76,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sensing anythi...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.47,0:04:49.22,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So is it okay to hide the truth then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:51.06,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's the way you always do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.97,0:04:55.02,Main Dialog Italic,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Hide? I'm not hiding anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.02,0:04:56.65,Main Dialog,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}That's the Defeated Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:05:00.11,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is there was a mysterious \Nexplosion in a TV studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.65,0:04:58.36,Main Dialog,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}What does {\i1}he{\i0} want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.27,0:05:04.24,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And at the time, Kaishou Rinroku \Nwas outside the studio door,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.24,0:05:05.45,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,which spared him from death.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.03,0:05:07.78,Main Dialog Italic,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That is also the truth... Or is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.20,0:05:10.28,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.78,0:05:14.00,Main Dialog Italic,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Now what if Mr. Kaishou was never \Nactually at the TV station?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.00,0:05:15.46,Main Dialog Italic,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.54,0:05:17.58,Main Dialog Italic,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Kaishou Rie...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:21.21,Main Dialog Italic,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,On the day of the explosion, \Nwhat did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.21,0:05:23.09,Main Dialog,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}He says Kaishou wasn't there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.75,0:05:23.84,Main Dialog,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Then what...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.09,0:05:24.26,Main Dialog Italic,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,This is insane!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:26.68,Main Dialog Italic,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,This is supposed to be \Nto prove his innocence!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:28.93,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Rie... Tell him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.76,0:05:35.02,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,That detective believes in you, as the \Ndaughter who can't bring herself to lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:34.35,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Family Maid (Head Maid)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:34.35,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Family Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.43,0:05:37.85,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,You need to live up \Nto his belief in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:49.20,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Right after the explosion \Nat the TV station...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.53,0:05:52.95,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I saw... my father at home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.95,0:05:53.66,Main Dialog Italic,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.66,0:05:54.66,Main Dialog Italic,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,At home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:55.33,Main Dialog Italic,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What does it mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.67,0:05:58.50,Main Dialog Italic,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.50,0:05:59.54,Main Dialog Italic,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Just because he was at home
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:01.54,Main Dialog Italic,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't mean he had anything \Nto do with the explosion!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.51,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,I examined the surveillance \Ncameras at the TV station,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.51,0:06:07.84,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,but there's no footage of Mr. \NKaishou Rinroku on that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:10.43,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,What if he arranged beforehand \Nwith people there,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.43,0:06:11.89,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,to tell the same story \Nthat he {\i1}was{\i0} present?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:13.64,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Motoyama Minami
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:13.64,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Television Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.89,0:06:14.01,Main Dialog,Motoyama,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you insinuating \NI'm an accomplice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.01,0:06:18.48,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying it's possible to trigger \Nan explosive from a safe place, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:19.81,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Koyama Izumi
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:19.81,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Public Prosecutor\N Joint Coordinating Dept.\N Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.48,0:06:20.31,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Objection! Objection!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.31,0:06:22.82,Main Dialog,Speaker,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a courtroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:29.86,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Inga
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:29.86,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Detective's Assistant
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:29.86,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Bettenou
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:29.32,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,As you wish...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.45,0:06:36.45,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,In the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.45,0:06:37.66,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,the cause of the explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.66,0:06:40.42,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,is currently being jointly investigated \Nby the military and police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.42,0:06:41.67,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,And this is unconfirmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.67,0:06:42.79,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,but a fragment from what appears to be
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:44.00,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,a surface-to-air missile \Nseems to have been found...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.00,0:06:45.84,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,A missile?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.84,0:06:48.67,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! That reminds me, back in 2001,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.67,0:06:50.34,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,one theory had it that \Npart of the Pentagon
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:53.10,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,was destroyed not by a \Npassenger jet, but a missile!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.10,0:06:55.93,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not talking about a conspiracy \Ntheory, but proof that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.93,0:06:58.23,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's from the same \Ntype of shoulder-launched SAM
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:07:01.10,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,that the Public Security \NForce is equipped with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.10,0:07:03.61,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,There were over 600 of them \Nprocured during the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.61,0:07:05.27,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Quite common, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.27,0:07:07.32,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,When did you... get that information?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.32,0:07:10.11,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you implying that the police \Nare fabricating evidence?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.40,0:07:12.36,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Did they do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.36,0:07:13.37,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.87,0:07:17.87,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to call one more \Nwitness to the stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.92,0:07:29.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Inga... What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.55,0:07:31.68,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You again?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.14,0:07:37.64,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Answer my question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.64,0:07:37.97,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.85,0:07:43.15,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear! You mustn't be violent!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.15,0:07:47.65,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,People have no choice but \Nto answer her question.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.65,0:07:48.86,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,Just one question...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:54.99,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what is actually \Nabsolutely unpardonable,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.99,0:07:58.49,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,yet you have no choice but to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:01.33,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.12,0:08:04.54,Main Dialog,Lady Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:20.06,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Just before the war began, Kaishou \NRinroku, the president of JJ Systems,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.06,0:08:24.02,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,sounded me out about providing software \Nfor the Public Prosecutors Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.02,0:08:31.69,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,That software could alter the last \Nupdate of computer files at will
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.69,0:08:34.36,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,and leave no traces behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.36,0:08:38.87,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,In short, the creation date of \Nconfiscated electronic documents
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.87,0:08:41.25,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,could be rewritten to establish a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.25,0:08:42.41,Main Dialog,Diet Member A,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop her!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.41,0:08:43.41,Main Dialog,Diet Member B,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.41,0:08:45.00,Main Dialog,Member,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}She's saying something important!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.96,0:08:47.92,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou was the only one \Nwith the software's key,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.00,0:08:47.42,Main Dialog,Diet Member A,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}This has nothing to do \Nwith this committee!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.42,0:08:47.92,Main Dialog,Member,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:49.13,Main Dialog,Member,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Shut her up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:50.17,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,and with his cooperation during the war,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.17,0:08:54.51,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,the police and prosecutors successfully \Ndealt with many political offenders, by...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.55,0:09:01.14,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Hayami Seigen
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.55,0:09:01.14,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Director of the Security Bureau \NMetropolitan Police Dept.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.10,0:08:59.10,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hayami-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.10,0:09:01.77,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,From now on, you shouldn't have \Nanything more to do with Kaishou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.77,0:09:03.06,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Consider your position...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.68,0:09:06.35,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What... What did I say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.12,0:09:26.17,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know this would \Nhappen... I'm sorr...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.63,0:09:34.72,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't lie, but said I was at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.63,0:09:40.68,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, Yuuki Shinjurou will \Ndefinitely deduce the presence of Bettenou...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:43.02,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Since he is a great detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:47.69,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,Rie, I was definitely at home, wasn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.00,0:10:11.79,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Inga!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.38,0:10:18.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.43,0:10:22.14,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,I want to eat souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.14,0:10:24.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,But you told me not to kill, Shinjurou!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:30.23,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pain to eat just \Nthe souls without killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:37.32,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying you're not \Ngonna stick with me anymore?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.00,0:10:56.09,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,The prosecutors still haven't built \Na case against that murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.21,0:10:59.01,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Fuwa Jujirou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.21,0:10:59.01,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Solar Power Advocate, Entrepreneur
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.09,0:10:57.26,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.26,0:11:00.76,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,And supposedly, they deny the \Nexistence of that altering software!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:03.89,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Fuwa, apparently you met \NMr. Kaishou on that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.35,0:11:08.10,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,Right. However, he was late \Nand soon left his seat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.10,0:11:09.98,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I knew something was \Nwrong when he left his seat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.98,0:11:12.60,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think back, it \Ncould've been a body double!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:15.19,Main Dialog,Nurse,0000,0000,0000,,The John Doe who came in yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.19,0:11:16.44,Main Dialog,Nurse,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get a good look?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:19.86,Main Dialog,Nurse,0000,0000,0000,,I came down, thinking I'd help prepare \Nthe body, but it's nowhere to be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.72,0:11:42.97,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.97,0:11:44.43,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Do you admit to the crimes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.43,0:11:48.10,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,What do you have to say about the \Nillegal program and the murders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.10,0:11:49.02,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.02,0:11:50.23,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Please explain!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.23,0:11:51.31,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Chairman Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.31,0:11:53.31,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,You have an obligation \Nto explain to the public!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.19,0:11:56.90,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,There's a place I want to stop by first.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.90,0:11:59.03,Main Dialog,Kaishou,0000,0000,0000,,You go thank the doctors.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.03,0:12:00.65,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,But Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.24,0:12:03.91,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou, please answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.91,0:12:04.62,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.91,0:12:04.62,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:05.95,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Mr. Kaishou, please answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.99,0:12:07.03,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,What's your relationship \Nwith the prosecutors?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:07.03,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Mihara Yasutarou
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:07.03,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Member of the Public Security Force,\NCommanded by Mizuno
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.03,0:12:09.79,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Is your backroom deal with \Nthe prosecutors finished?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.79,0:12:11.41,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,The net is having a field day with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:13.17,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Some posts even threaten to kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.37,0:12:15.29,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou, what's your \Nresponse to all of this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:15.29,Name White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuno Sakon
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.83,0:12:15.29,Name Sub White,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,Public Security Force Commander
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.09,0:12:17.04,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuno...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.67,0:12:22.30,Main Dialog,Mihara,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, please back off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.30,0:12:23.59,Main Dialog,Mihara,0000,0000,0000,,The car can't pull away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.59,0:12:24.55,Main Dialog,Public Security Force Member,0000,0000,0000,,Back up! Back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.55,0:12:25.55,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.55,0:12:26.80,Main Dialog,Public Security Force Member,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.80,0:12:28.10,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Chairman Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.10,0:12:29.18,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.18,0:12:30.52,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Are you running away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:44.20,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Father?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.20,0:12:45.36,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Jesus Christ!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.36,0:12:45.95,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Are they all right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.49,0:12:47.95,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.95,0:12:48.83,Main Dialog,Mihara,0000,0000,0000,,Call the firefighters!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.83,0:12:50.83,Main Dialog,Reporter,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! What's happening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.37,0:12:54.96,Main Dialog,Fuwa,0000,0000,0000,,He knew he couldn't escape, so \Ncommitted premeditated suicide...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.05,0:13:08.72,Main Dialog,Reporter 1,0000,0000,0000,,It's a solemn wake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.72,0:13:13.52,Main Dialog,Reporter 1,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku played such a \Nmajor role in postwar Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:16.19,Main Dialog,Reporter 2,0000,0000,0000,,If Mr. Kaishou did plan his own suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.19,0:13:21.69,Main Dialog,Reporter 2,0000,0000,0000,,then it's unforgivable that he also \Ntook the life of his driver, Mizuno Sakon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.65,0:13:27.32,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you done enough already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.32,0:13:28.62,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Defeated Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.62,0:13:29.87,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Izumi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:35.83,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.62,0:13:39.75,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You killed him, you bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.38,0:13:44.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Then... it was suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.01,0:13:51.97,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.97,0:13:56.44,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But the DNA of the bodies are a match \Nfor Mizuno and Chairman Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.06,0:14:01.48,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,You... and I... killed the Chairman!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.94,0:14:05.99,Main Dialog,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,What have I done...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:11.37,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.70,0:14:12.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Bettenou?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:15.00,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,There's no trace of that thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:17.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,She had to have been with Kaishou!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.33,0:14:19.04,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of my face, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.04,0:14:20.08,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,She had to have been with him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.08,0:14:21.21,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.79,0:14:23.05,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,This is not the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.63,0:14:30.34,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I noticed that all of the data on \Nmy father's computer was erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:32.39,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing left...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:36.43,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,So I think it might have been suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.43,0:14:39.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Was he the kind of man who would \Ndrag along Mizuno, his bodyguard?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:42.48,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know about my father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.53,0:14:49.74,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.74,0:14:55.20,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I wanted to know... I wanted \Nto know what he was really like,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.20,0:14:57.66,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,so maybe that's why I cooperated \Nwith you, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.16,0:15:00.92,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, it was pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.38,0:15:03.38,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Pointless?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.04,0:15:05.84,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,It's like my father said.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.30,0:15:08.59,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,There are as many truths \Nas there are people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.09,0:15:10.01,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Even you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.63,0:15:12.51,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.51,0:15:15.26,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,There are any number of \Ntruths you haven't shown me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.60,0:15:16.77,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What does that have to do with...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.77,0:15:20.27,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,That Inga woman... Who is she to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.60,0:15:24.52,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's... a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:29.57,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay. I have a lot of things \Nthat I can't tell you, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:36.08,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Father said that you'd "definitely \Ndeduce the presence of Bettenou."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.62,0:15:39.37,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,Blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.29,0:15:41.92,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.17,0:15:47.13,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I figured out that two \NKaishous meant Bettenou's power was at work...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.13,0:15:48.05,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.34,0:15:51.63,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Handkerchief...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.89,0:15:56.68,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:05.44,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Kaishou, on this sad occasion, I \Nreally, really, really feel for your loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.73,0:16:08.78,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,I just asked him to appear as a witness,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.78,0:16:11.40,Main Dialog,Mine,0000,0000,0000,,but this detective \Nstarted spouting off...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.11,0:16:13.20,Main Dialog,Rie,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.28,0:16:17.62,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it? Where did he put it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.62,0:16:20.54,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,If the vehicle's explosion \Nwasn't due to suicide,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.54,0:16:25.54,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,then candidates for murder are Fuwa \NJujirou, who survived the first blast,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:26.67,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Mihara Yasutarou,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.67,0:16:30.05,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,who became commander of the Public \NSecurity Force with Mizuno's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.05,0:16:31.59,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,and then there's the person \Nwho left the hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.59,0:16:32.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.59,0:16:36.60,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,How long has this handkerchief \Nbeen here?! How long?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.60,0:16:41.48,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly... The last time Inga \Nwas here, he left it behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.06,0:16:52.28,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But that same afternoon, I gave this \Nhandkerchief to Diet Member Kuramitsu Mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.03,0:16:55.32,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,When did Inga get this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.32,0:16:57.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,He's meeting with Kuramitsu Mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.74,0:16:58.91,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Where?! When?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.54,0:17:02.66,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of Diet Member Kuramitsu, \Nthere's something interesting about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.62,0:17:08.34,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,The Public Security Force commander, \NMizuno Sakon, who died with Mr. Kaishou,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.34,0:17:11.92,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,was her senior at university and \Napparently, they were close.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:16.34,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,You could've fooled me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:20.01,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I hack into the \Nuniversity's records?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.43,0:17:23.68,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Hacking... Kazamori!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.98,0:17:28.02,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember what Mizuno said \Nthe first time we met him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.94,0:17:30.36,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,"The Defeated Detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.36,0:17:33.19,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably the one who \Ntargeted Professor Kaishou."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.19,0:17:34.57,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,No, I mean after that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.41,0:17:37.66,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I'd make it more realistic...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:39.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind, just hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.12,0:17:43.83,Main Dialog,Kazamori,0000,0000,0000,,"Unusually enough, you were successful \Nwith Mr. Yajima's request. But..."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.83,0:17:47.33,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! That's what \Nkept gnawing at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.33,0:17:51.09,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,With Mr. Yajima's request, in the \Nend, foul play wasn't involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.09,0:17:53.09,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,So it wasn't reported in the press.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.09,0:17:55.88,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, he knew about it. How?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:07.23,Caption Top,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,President's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.23,0:18:09.10,Main Dialog,Oyamada,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.53,0:18:21.45,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Oyamada Arata
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.53,0:18:21.45,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Underground Software Dealer
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.66,0:18:21.20,Main Dialog,Oyamada,0000,0000,0000,,You wanna know something \Nabout that tune?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.20,0:18:24.66,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,It must be an old one. Doesn't seem \Nto exist in electronic form...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.12,0:18:30.83,Main Dialog,Oyamada,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, it's not an old song. In \Nfact, it just came out recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.51,0:18:43.22,Main Dialog,Oyamada,0000,0000,0000,,It's off of the unreleased \NYonagahime album.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.18,0:18:48.69,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know how to begin to apologize \Nfor what happened when you were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.02,0:18:49.94,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Okamoto Kankichi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.02,0:18:49.94,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}East Kantou Social Rehabilitation Program Center\N Director of Security
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.69,0:18:50.19,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,For us, it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.19,0:18:53.98,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that! Being here \Nwas a good experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.98,0:18:56.49,Main Dialog Italic,Kazamori (S),0000,0000,0000,,After all, you were \Nsurrounded by girls, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.99,0:18:59.11,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,After everything that's happened, \Nwhy do you want to talk to him {\i1}now{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.70,0:19:02.28,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very busy right now, \Nso consider this a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.91,0:19:06.16,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,He should know more about \NBettenou than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.79,0:19:07.96,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Bettenou...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.37,0:19:12.63,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still think that \NKaishou Rinroku had Bettenou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.59,0:19:17.30,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,If he did, faking his own \Ndeath would be child's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.97,0:19:20.55,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku is alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.82,0:19:37.61,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:43.74,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,All of these notes are about Bettenou...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:48.33,Main Dialog,Okamoto,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, writing stories \Nis allowed here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:50.25,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I first \Nencountered it by chance,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.12,0:19:53.33,Name,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Calls Himself a Novelist
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.12,0:19:53.33,Name Sub,Captions,0000,0000,0000,,{\a5}Prisoner
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.25,0:19:53.71,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I repeatedly performed experiments \Nand recorded the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.96,0:19:56.46,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,I tried everything that it could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:19:58.92,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.92,0:19:59.88,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.51,0:20:04.26,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,What's this "the living and the dead"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.14,0:20:07.18,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,That's the interesting thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.47,0:20:10.39,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Say, for instance, there's \Na living thing in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:12.85,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,It's difficult for that \Nthing you call "Bettenou"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.85,0:20:15.94,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,to give the illusion that it's a corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:16.98,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.98,0:20:19.23,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,The living talk and move.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.23,0:20:22.20,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,The brain is affected by its influence \Nthrough the senses of sight and hearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.20,0:20:25.16,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,But you're continuously \Nbeset by the "story"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:27.20,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,and its inconsistencies \Nyou receive from Bettenou.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.66,0:20:32.04,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,For example, I pretend \Nto be "Yuuki Shinjurou".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.58,0:20:35.83,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,But since you're looking at \Nthe real thing right there,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.83,0:20:38.38,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,your brain wouldn't be able to \Nwithstand the inconsistency of information.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.38,0:20:40.26,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,But what if there were an explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.26,0:20:42.17,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,in which the original body \Nwas rendered unrecognizable?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.17,0:20:44.55,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, in that case, it would be simple
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.55,0:20:48.06,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,to make the people involved \Nthink that the corpse was yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.68,0:20:51.35,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,What's necessary is making \Nthem hear your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.35,0:20:56.11,Main Dialog,Novelist,0000,0000,0000,,And by visually perceiving Bettenou, special \Nreceptors are produced in the brain...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.98,0:21:00.23,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.23,0:21:05.78,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou Rinroku used Bettenou's power \Nto commit murder and fake his own death?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.53,0:21:09.54,Main Dialog,Hayami,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.45,0:21:14.46,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\a7}Yuuki Shinjurou
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.54,0:21:13.12,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,An invitation to a party was delivered \Nto the office this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.12,0:21:14.54,Main Dialog,Shinjurou,0000,0000,0000,,The sender was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:20.00,Caption Top,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Kaishou
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:36.10,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,In the pale morning \Nmist, a whispered prayer
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.48,0:21:44.11,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna follow this \Ntwisted landscape with you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.53,0:21:52.12,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for the "truth", \N"a 'lie' will do" is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.45,0:22:00.50,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Tracing it as if we can see through
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.50,0:22:04.42,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, beyond words
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:08.43,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a falling feather
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.43,0:22:11.43,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.35,0:22:16.85,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:36.29,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, unravel it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.29,0:22:40.42,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Like a tattered cloud
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.42,0:22:43.25,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for, find it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.13,0:22:48.47,Song,Ending Song,0000,0000,0000,,So we can cuddle close together here
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.55,0:22:53.14,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,But the thing called "truth" \Ndoesn't really exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.14,0:22:56.39,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, "truth" is just something \Nthat's always being searched out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.39,0:22:58.35,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,People look for the \N"truth" for eternity,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.35,0:23:00.85,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,but the "truth" is eternally ephemeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.85,0:23:03.11,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,The quest for "truth" \Nbrings it into existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.11,0:23:06.57,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,but it is an object through which its \Nexistence proves its non-existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.57,0:23:08.70,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,When the "truth" occurs \Nin this physical world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.70,0:23:11.45,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,humans have already ceased \Nto be human, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.45,0:23:13.58,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,From "I Give Reason".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:16.83,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on UN-GO: \N"I'm Just Searching".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:16.87,Title,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Just Searching
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:16.87,Source,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,Inspired by "Sneering Demon" and "Red Trap" from Ango Sakaguchi's\NMeijikaika Ango Torimonochou\N(Meiji-era Detective Stories)\Nand from "I Give Reason"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.41,0:23:19.54,Main Dialog,Inga,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Shinjurou... This is the end.
